K-Tel is a company based in Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada, which has been in business since the late 1960s and which for many years specialized in selling consumer products through infomercials and live demonstration. It is known as the originator of the "As Seen On TV" type of marketing strategy. Its products include compilation music albums, including The Super Hits series, The Dynamic Hits series and The Number One Hits series and consumer products, including The Record Selector, Veg-O-Matic, Miracle Brush, and The Feather Touch Knife. The company has sold more than half a billion units world wide.
K-Tel has subsidiaries or other controlled entities in the U.S. and the UK. In the UK, the company is known as "K-Tel UK Limited." In the U.S. and Canada, it is known as "K-Tel International," with U.S.-distributed compilation albums distributed from Plymouth, Minnesota.


